th Chevron at 715k L/S. We allocated the final bunker hedge result to this voyage which is lsmgo ($1,540) and Vlsfo ($22,500) in losses. Bunkers consumed on this voyage are still the expensive $996 VLSFO from last bunkering since its FIFO but latest bunkering we received VLSFO $830 pmt which makes sense Vs paper prices results here.\n\nIn short the total hedge of this CVC is profitable VS physical prices we consumed. Or more simply put total Hedge profit is $36,000 usd. \nOnly discrepancy we did not foresee is the underconsumption and quick turns arounds which have made it so that bunkers burnt were not matching with paper price at time of performing the voyage. Ie, the cheaper VLSFO which we last bunkered will only start kicking in on next voyage ie, voyage #2216 and thus matching the paper loss here mentioned on this voyage. \n\nOtherwise, straight forward CVC with chevron at fix rate/dem and no waiting time between voyages.\n\nVessel\tStena Performance\nVoy#\t2215\nFix#\tCVX CVC #6 USG/CBS\nC/P Date\tMay 19, 2022\nCharterer\tCHEVRON\nBroker\tAFFINITY\nStart\tBahia Las Minas\nLoad\tPascagoula\nDischarge\tBahia Las Minas\nCargo\t45,000 mt CPP\nLay/Can\tAug 22-24, 2022 (00:00-00:00)\nRate\t$715,000\nComm\tCharterer: 2.5%, Broker: 1.25%, Agent: 1%\nTCE\nPnL\t$12,328.62 for 13.9 days\n(44k) Bss 15,5 pd\nDemurrage\t$21,500.00"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-08-25T19:03:09.917","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"earnings updated basis actual earlier arrival and estimated demurrage"}],"offhireList":[{"id":192480,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":100876,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}